Reasoning: The paper deals with signal processing and estimation techniques for direction of arrival (DOA) using nonuniform linear arrays. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of sparse recovery algorithms, which is a popular topic in compressed sensing (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper analyzes the noise statistics of the co-prime arrays, which could fall under the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
